WEBVTT

00:11.576 --> 00:14.057
- Thanks for meeting me, Kevin.

00:14.101 --> 00:15.798
- Yeah, sure thing.

00:15.841 --> 00:18.279
- Please, have a seat.

00:18.322 --> 00:20.150
So I have been
reviewing the evidence

00:20.194 --> 00:21.717
in the Doyle homicide case,

00:21.760 --> 00:24.241
and I just wanted to

00:24.285 --> 00:26.156
touch base with you

00:26.200 --> 00:28.289
one more time.

00:28.332 --> 00:30.247
- I'm not sure
what you're asking.

00:30.291 --> 00:31.683
- I'm asking
if there's anything

00:31.727 --> 00:34.164
you would like to add

00:34.208 --> 00:36.166
or modify.

00:36.210 --> 00:38.081
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:38.125 --> 00:40.083
- No.

00:40.127 --> 00:43.173
I stand by
my original statement.

00:43.217 --> 00:45.349
- Yo, what's in the bag?

00:45.393 --> 00:46.611
- Nothing.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.744
- Hey, I'm police.

00:48.787 --> 00:50.789
I asked you a question.

00:50.833 --> 00:53.183
<i>- Officer Doyle
had no probable cause</i>

00:53.227 --> 00:55.533
<i>hopping out of the car
and stopping Shawn Paige.</i>

00:55.577 --> 00:59.407
<i>Doyle was the aggressor,
not Paige.</i>

00:59.450 --> 01:00.538
That man was walking down
the street

01:00.582 --> 01:01.887
minding his own business.

01:01.931 --> 01:04.107
- So the two men inside
of the recording studio

01:04.151 --> 01:05.456
<i>who shot and killed Doyle...</i>

01:05.500 --> 01:07.284
- Doyle!

01:07.328 --> 01:09.678
<i>- You believe they were acting
in self-defense?</i>

01:09.721 --> 01:11.593
[gunshots]

01:11.636 --> 01:13.551
- Yes, ma'am.

01:14.378 --> 01:15.901
I need you to fight, Doyle.
I need you to fight.

01:15.945 --> 01:17.207
<i>- Okay.</i>

01:17.251 --> 01:20.384
Then I guess I need to file
a motion to dismiss.

01:20.428 --> 01:21.429
- That's your call.

01:21.472 --> 01:23.213
- No, it's actually your call.

01:23.257 --> 01:24.606
You were the only witness.

01:24.649 --> 01:27.522
So if you think Doyle is
to blame, there is no case.

01:27.565 --> 01:29.524
- Like I said,

01:29.567 --> 01:32.135
I stand by
my original statement.

01:32.179 --> 01:34.224
- It takes a lot of guts
for a young Black cop

01:34.268 --> 01:35.660
<i>to take on the Chicago
Police Department.</i>

01:35.704 --> 01:37.532
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:37.575 --> 01:41.666
- I'm right here!
I'm right here!

01:41.710 --> 01:44.669
<i>- I know what's been going on
with Atwater past few weeks.</i>

01:44.713 --> 01:46.367
- I got no idea
what you're talking about.

01:46.410 --> 01:48.456
- Kenny.

01:48.499 --> 01:51.241
Please don't make a jerk of me,
okay?

01:51.285 --> 01:53.548
We both know what you've
been doing has gotta stop now

01:53.591 --> 01:55.071
before someone gets hurt.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.768
- Like I said, I don't know
what you're talking about,

01:56.812 --> 01:58.553
but even if I did,

01:58.596 --> 02:00.337
there's no way
I could agree to that.

02:00.381 --> 02:03.253
That kid Atwater broke
the most sacred rule there is:

02:03.297 --> 02:05.386
he snitched on the police

02:05.429 --> 02:07.562
on a cop who died
on the line of duty

02:07.605 --> 02:09.738
with a wife
and two little kids.

02:09.781 --> 02:11.566
If that's not bad enough,

02:11.609 --> 02:14.221
state's attorney's office
just dropped the case.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.179
The two punks
that killed Doyle,

02:16.223 --> 02:17.876
a Chicago police officer,

02:17.920 --> 02:19.226
are gonna walk free.

02:19.269 --> 02:20.792
- Atwater did
what he thought was right.

02:20.836 --> 02:24.274
- No.
He crossed the line.

02:24.318 --> 02:25.797
Blue wall is there
to keep us together.

02:25.841 --> 02:27.712
It keeps us safe.

02:27.756 --> 02:29.453
It's a bible,
our Ten Commandments.

02:29.497 --> 02:31.586
You of all people
know that, Hank.

02:31.629 --> 02:34.545
If someone chooses
to violate that code,

02:34.589 --> 02:37.200
he's gotta pay the price.

02:37.244 --> 02:38.854
Way it's always been.

02:38.897 --> 02:41.422
<i>♪ </i>

02:41.465 --> 02:42.988
Way it always will be.

02:43.032 --> 02:50.170
<i>♪ </i>

02:54.870 --> 02:57.568
- You know, Lisa,
I signed a statement

02:57.612 --> 02:59.657
with the state's attorney.

02:59.701 --> 03:01.572
Your husband
will be exonerated.

03:03.444 --> 03:05.489
- [sighs]
I can't believe it.

03:05.533 --> 03:08.231
I really can't.

03:08.275 --> 03:11.669
It's the best damn thing
I've heard in a long time.

03:11.713 --> 03:13.323
- It's good news for you too.

03:13.367 --> 03:15.717
That means that lawsuit against
the city just got a lot better.

03:15.760 --> 03:17.545
Proves that cop Doyle
was in the wrong;

03:17.588 --> 03:19.242
your husband Shawn
was in the right.

03:21.679 --> 03:23.203
- [sighs]

03:25.335 --> 03:26.902
Thank you.

03:28.730 --> 03:30.732
- Glad I could help.

03:33.604 --> 03:36.303
- You know, brother, this city
needs more people like you.

03:38.087 --> 03:39.654
People who actually care.

03:39.697 --> 03:42.222
Know how to treat people
like people.

03:44.311 --> 03:45.834
- Ay.

03:45.877 --> 03:48.271
I got you, little homie.

03:49.403 --> 03:50.926
Feel real sorry
about your father.

03:50.969 --> 03:53.711
He was a good man.
He did nothing wrong.

03:53.755 --> 03:56.714
- Then why'd you kill him?

04:02.938 --> 04:04.940
- [sighs]

04:09.597 --> 04:13.731
[tires squealing]

04:13.775 --> 04:16.734
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

04:16.778 --> 04:23.785
<i>♪ </i>

04:28.920 --> 04:31.096
I'm telling you,
I'm starting to get paranoid.

04:31.140 --> 04:32.576
Like, for real.

04:32.620 --> 04:34.926
Every time I see a cop,
I get nervous.

04:34.970 --> 04:37.581
I start thinking,
my mind starts racing.

04:37.625 --> 04:40.367
I told you I was literally
on my knees

04:40.410 --> 04:42.412
looking under the damn car.
For what?

04:42.456 --> 04:43.848
I don't know,
but I was looking.

04:43.892 --> 04:46.024
- How many officers
were in the car?

04:46.068 --> 04:48.113
- What do you mean?
- I'm just asking.

04:48.157 --> 04:49.724
- One.
Why?

04:49.767 --> 04:51.900
- Well, if someone was
gonna plant something,

04:51.943 --> 04:53.858
I'm guessing, you know,

04:53.902 --> 04:56.121
they would do it alone and
leave their partner out of it.

04:56.165 --> 04:58.515
- [sighs]

04:58.559 --> 05:00.082
You're saying that--

05:00.125 --> 05:03.390
- I'm saying that, you know,
Doyle's crew, they play dirty.

05:04.565 --> 05:06.436
- [sighs]

05:11.006 --> 05:13.400
[sighs]

05:13.443 --> 05:15.793
Sorry for dragging you
into all into this, Ruz.

05:15.837 --> 05:18.143
[exhales]

05:18.187 --> 05:20.711
This nonsense is starting
to get to me.

05:20.755 --> 05:22.365
Am I going crazy,

05:22.409 --> 05:25.412
or is this actually happening?

05:25.455 --> 05:26.630
- Hey?
- Hm?

05:26.674 --> 05:29.764
- Hand me that rag.
- What?

05:32.506 --> 05:35.465
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:35.509 --> 05:41.471
<i>♪ </i>

05:41.515 --> 05:42.820
- It's heroin.

05:42.864 --> 05:45.040
- What the hell?

05:46.824 --> 05:48.565
- Well,

05:48.609 --> 05:51.394
at least we know
you're not crazy.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.135
- Damn.

05:53.178 --> 05:55.877
- Well, what's the plan?

05:55.920 --> 05:58.488
You gonna inventory
and write paper?

05:58.532 --> 06:01.404
- I don't know.
I'm still thinking about it.

06:01.448 --> 06:02.840
- Did you get a good look
at the patrol car?

06:02.884 --> 06:05.365
You see V-tags, plates?

06:06.757 --> 06:09.847
All right, we can pull
POD footage,

06:09.891 --> 06:11.501
scroll through the video.
Who knows?

06:11.545 --> 06:13.851
Maybe we catch this dirty prick
actually planting the dope.

06:15.244 --> 06:17.202
- It's possible,

06:17.246 --> 06:19.509
but these dudes
are all over the place.

06:19.553 --> 06:20.989
Doyle's probably got
two cousins and an uncle

06:21.032 --> 06:22.860
working for IED,

06:22.904 --> 06:24.427
which means no matter
what we find,

06:24.471 --> 06:26.603
the case still won't go
anywhere, and you know that.

06:30.564 --> 06:31.695
- All right.

06:31.739 --> 06:33.871
Well, you do what you gotta do,

06:33.915 --> 06:36.134
but you remember that I'm here
to help you, all right?

06:36.178 --> 06:38.485
Any way you want.

06:40.051 --> 06:42.706
- Appreciate that.

06:45.274 --> 06:48.059
<i>- Police officers will spend
more time in the streets</i>

06:48.103 --> 06:49.539
<i>and in the neighborhoods.</i>

06:49.583 --> 06:52.237
- Hey, Deputy Supe's
giving a speech.

06:52.281 --> 06:54.196
- You mean apology.

06:54.239 --> 06:55.589
She's pretty much telling us

06:55.632 --> 06:57.460
we're a bunch
of unenlightened idiots.

06:57.504 --> 06:58.853
- I wouldn't go that far.

06:58.896 --> 07:00.115
She's just telling us
what we already know.

07:00.158 --> 07:02.030
Police have to do a better job
at deescalating.

07:02.073 --> 07:05.120
- Sure, but she doesn't have
to be so disrespectful.

07:05.163 --> 07:06.513
We're all trying our best.

07:06.556 --> 07:08.471
- Not good enough, Hailey.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.734
It isn't.

07:10.778 --> 07:13.041
CPD did not kill George Floyd,
I get that,

07:13.084 --> 07:15.913
but we sure as hell killed
Shawn Paige.

07:15.957 --> 07:18.481
So maybe we should
just reserve our judgement,

07:18.525 --> 07:19.743
listen to what the sister
has to say.

07:19.787 --> 07:21.963
- Yeah, I'm not...

07:23.617 --> 07:26.184
<i>- We will once and for all
tear down the blue wall.</i>

07:30.885 --> 07:34.062
- [sighs]

07:34.105 --> 07:36.499
Nice to meet you, Sergeant.
[chuckles]

07:36.543 --> 07:38.109
- Nice to meet you.
- I know you're busy.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.502
I really appreciate you
coming in here

07:39.546 --> 07:41.852
to meet me in person.

07:41.896 --> 07:44.028
- Deputy Supe calls, you come.

07:44.072 --> 07:46.204
- Please, call me Sam.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.642
You want anything to drink?
Coffee, water?

07:48.685 --> 07:49.904
- No thanks.

07:49.947 --> 07:52.559
- You know, I've been here
just two weeks,

07:52.602 --> 07:54.517
and all I keep hearing
is your name.

07:54.561 --> 07:57.215
Hank Voight this,
Hank Voight that.

07:57.259 --> 08:00.784
By all accounts,
you are one hell of a cop.

08:00.828 --> 08:02.612
- Well, that is
very kind of you,

08:02.656 --> 08:03.961
but I'm guessing
you didn't call me down here

08:04.005 --> 08:05.006
to blow smoke.

08:05.049 --> 08:08.052
- No.
I didn't.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.880
I wanted to give you
a heads up, cop to cop.

08:11.186 --> 08:12.970
If you keep running your unit
the way you've been doing

08:13.014 --> 08:14.145
for the past seven years,

08:14.189 --> 08:16.670
you're gonna be out of a job
by Christmas.

08:18.149 --> 08:20.238
- Anything else I should know?

08:20.282 --> 08:22.545
- Yeah.

08:22.589 --> 08:25.156
I'm on your side.

08:25.200 --> 08:27.115
I want you to succeed,
Sergeant.

08:27.158 --> 08:28.377
[phone buzzes]

08:28.420 --> 08:30.988
If Hank Voight can change
the way he polices,

08:31.032 --> 08:33.948
if he can learn how
to play by the rules,

08:33.991 --> 08:36.516
the rest of the department
will follow.

08:40.215 --> 08:41.782
- Look,
thanks for the heads up,

08:41.825 --> 08:43.827
but I gotta go
if that's all right.

08:43.871 --> 08:46.526
5-year-old girl just got shot.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.794
- Stay safe, Sergeant.

08:53.837 --> 08:56.013
- Ma'am.

08:56.057 --> 08:57.188
- Hang in there.
You're gonna be okay.

08:57.232 --> 08:58.538
- [crying]
- We were walking back

08:58.581 --> 08:59.887
from the market, and then
I heard two loud pops,

08:59.930 --> 09:01.279
and I saw Laura
on the ground bleeding.

09:01.323 --> 09:02.585
- Okay, did you see
the shooter?

09:02.629 --> 09:03.673
- No.

09:03.717 --> 09:04.674
- Did you see anything
suspicious?

09:04.718 --> 09:05.893
- No, no, no, no, no.
I just--

09:05.936 --> 09:07.851
We were just walking,
and then she got hit.

09:07.895 --> 09:09.070
Listen, I need to be
with my little girl right now.

09:09.113 --> 09:11.638
- Okay, go.
- Okay, what do we know?

09:11.681 --> 09:12.987
- Not much.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.858
Jay and I heard
the "shots fired" call

09:14.902 --> 09:16.294
come over the radio,
so we rushed to the scene.

09:16.338 --> 09:18.079
The little girl was
bleeding out when we got here.

09:18.122 --> 09:19.167
- She got shot in the stomach.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.385
Good news is,
the ambo got here quick.

09:20.429 --> 09:22.823
- What happened?
Robbery, drive-by?

09:22.866 --> 09:24.128
- Yeah, we don't know.

09:24.172 --> 09:26.087
She was walking
with her parents,

09:26.130 --> 09:27.218
and then she got shot somehow.

09:27.262 --> 09:28.480
Unfortunately,
they didn't see much.

09:28.524 --> 09:30.047
They heard two loud pops.
Next thing you know,

09:30.091 --> 09:31.135
their daughter's
on the ground bleeding.

09:31.179 --> 09:33.050
- So stray bullet?
- Sounds like it.

09:33.094 --> 09:34.704
- All right,
so start canvassing.

09:34.748 --> 09:37.838
Talk to witnesses, pull PODs,
surveillance cameras.

09:37.881 --> 09:39.883
Find someone who saw something.

09:44.932 --> 09:48.065
- I hope Kev didn't think
that I...

09:48.109 --> 09:50.111
I was bitchin' about
the Deputy Supe's speech,

09:50.154 --> 09:52.330
not trying to minimize
what happened to Shawn Paige.

09:52.374 --> 09:54.289
- I think
he totally knows that.

09:54.332 --> 09:55.420
He's just venting.

09:55.464 --> 09:56.639
He's going through so much
right now.

09:56.683 --> 09:59.337
I wouldn't worry about it.
- Okay.

09:59.381 --> 10:01.775
- Sir, do you live around here?

10:01.818 --> 10:03.646
Yeah?
Did you see anything unusual?

10:03.690 --> 10:04.952
Anybody with a gun,
anyone arguing?

10:04.995 --> 10:05.996
- No.

10:06.040 --> 10:08.259
- Did you hear gunshots?
- No.

10:08.303 --> 10:10.348
- How long you been out here?
- About an hour.

10:10.392 --> 10:12.350
- You've been out here
for an hour and you didn't hear

10:12.394 --> 10:13.700
two gunshots
that hit a little girl

10:13.743 --> 10:14.744
right over there
30 minutes ago?

10:14.788 --> 10:16.093
- I already told you.

10:16.137 --> 10:17.660
- Look, we're just trying
to get some information.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.314
- And I ain't got any, so get
the hell out my face, bitch.

10:19.357 --> 10:21.011
- What did you say to me?

10:26.321 --> 10:27.714
- Come on.

10:29.977 --> 10:31.195
- Yeah, y'all racist-ass cops

10:31.239 --> 10:33.067
ain't welcome
around here no more.

10:36.244 --> 10:39.508
[both speaking Spanish]

10:43.338 --> 10:44.774
- Hey, man.

10:44.818 --> 10:46.689
You see the shooting today?

10:46.733 --> 10:49.213
Maybe hear gunshots
about 30 minutes ago?

10:49.257 --> 10:50.998
See an argument, fight,

10:51.041 --> 10:52.390
car drive by real fast?

10:52.434 --> 10:53.870
Anything like that?

10:55.089 --> 10:56.481
All right.

10:56.525 --> 10:57.961
- No, no, no,
what are you doing?

10:58.005 --> 10:59.136
Hey, stop.
What are you doing?

10:59.180 --> 11:00.311
- He just threw
a beer bottle at me.

11:00.355 --> 11:01.356
- Let it go.

11:01.399 --> 11:02.444
It's not worth
escalating this.

11:02.487 --> 11:03.706
Let it go.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.926
- That's Agg Assault
against a police officer.

11:05.969 --> 11:07.318
All right, they can film
all they want.

11:07.362 --> 11:08.885
I don't care.
- I do care.

11:08.929 --> 11:10.713
I'm not risking my career
over a damn beer bottle.

11:10.757 --> 11:12.802
You let it go, okay?

11:15.979 --> 11:17.851
- [sighs]

11:20.462 --> 11:22.725
- Okay, what do we know?
- Nothing much.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.161
No shot splatter,
no shell casings,

11:24.205 --> 11:25.467
no witnesses.

11:25.510 --> 11:27.164
- None that were willing
to cooperate anyway.

11:27.208 --> 11:28.296
- I just talked to Med.

11:28.339 --> 11:29.732
The girl, Laura Diaz,
she's in critical,

11:29.776 --> 11:31.516
but the good news is,
doctors removed the bullet.

11:31.560 --> 11:33.301
It's 9mm.
It's with ballistics right now.

11:33.344 --> 11:34.737
- Not sure if it's connected,

11:34.781 --> 11:36.173
but Laura's father
was arrested for possession

11:36.217 --> 11:37.305
three years ago.

11:37.348 --> 11:38.523
Also has some gang cards
on file.

11:38.567 --> 11:40.177
Looks like he runs
with the Latin Players.

11:40.221 --> 11:41.352
- Maybe we were wrong.

11:41.396 --> 11:43.224
Maybe it wasn't a stray bullet
after all.

11:44.965 --> 11:46.401
- You're saying
that I was the target,

11:46.444 --> 11:47.968
and they hit Laura by accident?

11:48.011 --> 11:50.057
- No, what we're saying is,

11:50.100 --> 11:52.189
we know about your affiliation
with the Latin Players.

11:52.233 --> 11:53.800
- What the hell
are you talking about?

11:53.843 --> 11:56.237
- Roberto, we're just trying
to find the person

11:56.280 --> 11:57.455
who shot your daughter.

11:57.499 --> 11:58.805
We're here not here
to investigate you.

11:58.848 --> 11:59.893
We don't care who you run with.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.808
- I don't run with anyone.
[scoffs]

12:01.851 --> 12:04.071
I own a bakery
in Little Village

12:04.114 --> 12:06.290
on 26th street.
I work there seven days a week.

12:06.334 --> 12:08.771
- We also know about
your prior arrest.

12:08.815 --> 12:11.556
- I got pulled over by a cop
for running a stop sign,

12:11.600 --> 12:13.950
and I had two joints
in my glove compartment, okay?

12:13.994 --> 12:15.822
That don't make me
no drug dealer, bro,

12:15.865 --> 12:17.911
and that sure as hell
don't make me no gangbanger.

12:17.954 --> 12:19.739
- Okay, it's our mistake.

12:20.957 --> 12:22.567
But like I said,

12:22.611 --> 12:24.221
we're just trying to find the
person who shot your daughter.

12:24.265 --> 12:26.571
- So think hard.

12:26.615 --> 12:29.531
Roberto, as difficult
as this must be,

12:29.574 --> 12:31.315
put yourself back
in that moment in time

12:31.359 --> 12:32.882
when you heard the gunshots.

12:32.926 --> 12:34.144
Was there anybody around?

12:34.188 --> 12:37.321
Anybody walking?
Running?

12:37.365 --> 12:40.020
- Naw.

12:40.063 --> 12:42.022
- You see any cars?
Motorcycles?

12:42.065 --> 12:43.806
Bicycles?

12:43.850 --> 12:45.895
- I heard a car drive away,
like, real fast,

12:45.939 --> 12:48.202
but it was through the alleyway
at the other end of the block.

12:48.245 --> 12:50.247
- All right, you remember
the make and model, the color?

12:50.291 --> 12:52.075
- It was dark, man.

12:52.119 --> 12:53.424
It was, like, black I think.

12:53.468 --> 12:55.862
- Thank you.
That helps.

12:57.951 --> 12:59.909
- Yeah.

12:59.953 --> 13:02.259
Listen, I'll do whatever I can,
it's just...

13:02.303 --> 13:03.957
go find this son of a bitch.

13:08.483 --> 13:11.225
- Okay, black car

13:11.268 --> 13:14.141
drove off right after
the gunshots.

13:14.184 --> 13:16.099
Cool.
Copy that.

13:16.143 --> 13:17.318
All right, that's Halstead.

13:17.361 --> 13:18.928
He's gonna pull more
surveillance video.

13:18.972 --> 13:20.277
- Okay.
- Try to find a black car.

13:20.321 --> 13:21.931
- Good.

13:21.975 --> 13:24.586
I heard they dropped
the homicide charge

13:24.629 --> 13:28.068
against those two bangers
who shot Doyle.

13:28.111 --> 13:29.852
- It was a weak case.
- Mm-hmm.

13:29.896 --> 13:33.029
- Bangers or not, that night,

13:33.073 --> 13:34.596
just two dudes minding
their own business.

13:34.639 --> 13:37.207
- Yeah, look.

13:37.251 --> 13:39.079
Kevin...

13:42.909 --> 13:45.825
I know you've been going
through a lot, okay?

13:47.348 --> 13:49.959
But you gotta understand,
these cops,

13:50.003 --> 13:53.223
I mean, this is gonna
rile them up even more.

13:53.267 --> 13:55.965
The only thing they were
hanging onto was that trial,

13:56.009 --> 13:58.663
watching those two offenders
get convicted of murder.

13:58.707 --> 14:01.405
- I get it,
but that's their problem.

14:01.449 --> 14:03.668
And like I've
been trying to say,

14:03.712 --> 14:05.888
those two dudes
weren't really offenders.

14:05.932 --> 14:07.150
- Oh, come on, man,
you don't have--

14:07.194 --> 14:08.325
- The charges got dropped.

14:08.369 --> 14:10.066
- Kevin, I'm trying
to help you.

14:13.635 --> 14:16.159
If you ever need to talk...

14:17.073 --> 14:19.902
- I'm good.

14:19.946 --> 14:21.208
Thanks.

14:23.384 --> 14:26.343
<i>[somber music]</i>

14:26.387 --> 14:33.394
<i>♪ </i>

14:37.920 --> 14:39.922
- This security camera caught
our masked offender

14:39.966 --> 14:41.054
running down the alley.

14:41.097 --> 14:43.317
Then an unknown male
chases after him,

14:43.360 --> 14:44.622
confronts him, they fight,

14:44.666 --> 14:45.928
our offender draws a weapon.

14:45.972 --> 14:47.538
I'm guessing that's our 9mm.

14:47.582 --> 14:49.366
He fires two rounds,
misses his intended target.

14:49.410 --> 14:52.587
- And it hits a 5-year-old girl
named Laura Diaz a block away.

14:52.630 --> 14:54.589
- The question is: where was
the offender coming from,

14:54.632 --> 14:55.807
and who did he rob?

14:55.851 --> 14:57.635
- Can you enhance that?

14:57.679 --> 15:01.117
[keys clacking]

15:01.161 --> 15:02.945
Is that a church?

15:02.989 --> 15:05.992
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:06.035 --> 15:13.042
<i>♪ </i>

15:18.526 --> 15:21.572
- Chicago PD.
Anyone here?

15:21.616 --> 15:23.879
- Hello?

15:31.713 --> 15:33.628
Hello?

15:33.671 --> 15:34.934
- Police.

15:38.024 --> 15:41.375
- Hello?
Jay.

15:41.418 --> 15:42.898
Sir?

15:44.204 --> 15:45.509
- [heavy breathing]
- Sir, sir, it's okay.

15:45.553 --> 15:47.511
We're the police.
It's okay.

15:47.555 --> 15:49.383
- You want us to call
an ambulance?

15:49.426 --> 15:50.471
- No.

15:50.514 --> 15:51.733
- Do you need medical help?
You sure?

15:51.776 --> 15:53.039
- I'm okay.

15:53.082 --> 15:54.997
- All right,
let's get you up, okay?

15:55.041 --> 15:56.564
You got it?
Come on.

15:56.607 --> 15:58.000
- [grunts]

15:58.044 --> 15:59.132
I'm okay, I'm okay, I'm okay.

15:59.175 --> 16:01.134
- All right.

16:03.875 --> 16:05.877
You wanna tell us
what happened?

16:05.921 --> 16:08.619
- Hold on.
I need a drink.

16:10.839 --> 16:13.537
That's the last time I stash
money for a drug dealer.

16:13.581 --> 16:15.800
That's for damn sure.

16:19.065 --> 16:20.892
I'm not proud
of keeping dirty cash,

16:20.936 --> 16:23.983
but I won't apologize
for it either.

16:24.026 --> 16:26.681
I did what I had to do
to keep the doors open,

16:26.724 --> 16:28.726
give the people in this parish
a place to come,

16:28.770 --> 16:30.119
a place to pray.

16:30.163 --> 16:32.426
- Yeah, look, we're not here
to judge or absolve.

16:32.469 --> 16:34.776
We just wanna know
what happened.

16:34.819 --> 16:37.039
- I was in here
doing paperwork.

16:37.083 --> 16:39.041
I look up.
I see some guy in a mask

16:39.085 --> 16:41.130
pointing a gun at me,
telling me to open the safe,

16:41.174 --> 16:43.698
like he knew I was hiding
all this cash.

16:43.741 --> 16:44.960
I did what he said.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.658
I gave him the money,
and he ran out.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.747
But then I realized the dealer
would think I was involved,

16:49.791 --> 16:52.446
so I ran after the guy.
I tackled him.

16:52.489 --> 16:53.751
He tried to shoot me,

16:53.795 --> 16:56.885
but anyway,
he ran away and drove off.

16:56.928 --> 16:59.192
- Well then, he drove off,

16:59.235 --> 17:01.194
so who tied you up
and beat you?

17:01.237 --> 17:02.586
- The dealer.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.501
I called him up.
I told him what happened.

17:04.545 --> 17:06.721
Next thing I know,
he's in my office punching me,

17:06.764 --> 17:07.983
calling me a thief.

17:08.027 --> 17:10.768
- All right,
what's the dealer's name?

17:10.812 --> 17:12.770
- Hey.

17:12.814 --> 17:14.076
A little girl got shot

17:14.120 --> 17:17.036
'cause you were hiding
drug money in a church.

17:17.079 --> 17:20.039
So you need
to start talking now.

17:22.215 --> 17:24.173
- Carlos, I don't care
about you,

17:24.217 --> 17:27.263
the cash, the priest,
or the church.

17:27.307 --> 17:29.526
I just wanna find the guy

17:29.570 --> 17:32.138
who did the robbery
and shot that little girl.

17:32.181 --> 17:35.532
Now you ask me, we're on the
same side on this thing, bro.

17:35.576 --> 17:37.665
- What are you saying?

17:37.708 --> 17:40.537
- I'm saying I'll find him, and
then I'll put him in prison,

17:40.581 --> 17:42.104
and I'm done.

17:42.148 --> 17:44.541
You're free to do
whatever you gotta do.

17:47.283 --> 17:49.242
Okay, who else knew
about the money?

17:49.285 --> 17:50.591
- Nobody.

17:50.634 --> 17:52.114
- No friends?
Business associates?

17:52.158 --> 17:53.811
- [chuckles]
They all criminals, man.

17:53.855 --> 17:55.161
- Hmm.

17:55.204 --> 17:57.032
- Why would I tell them
where I hide my cash?

17:57.076 --> 17:58.990
- So you telling me
only you and Father Allende

17:59.034 --> 18:00.514
knew about the money
in the church?

18:00.557 --> 18:01.819
- Yeah, that's why
I beat his ass.

18:01.863 --> 18:02.820
- Hmm.

18:02.864 --> 18:03.908
- He's playing me like a fool.

18:03.952 --> 18:06.302
- No.
His story checks out.

18:06.346 --> 18:07.912
After the guy took the money,

18:07.956 --> 18:10.654
he ran out,
Allende chased after him,

18:10.698 --> 18:12.308
tackled the guy.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.136
He turned around,
got off two shots,

18:14.180 --> 18:15.137
almost killed the priest.

18:15.181 --> 18:16.921
Got the whole thing
on tape too.

18:16.965 --> 18:19.620
Sound like an inside job
to you?

18:19.663 --> 18:21.143
Uh-huh.

18:21.187 --> 18:24.233
So who else knew about
the money in the church?

18:24.277 --> 18:26.801
- I'm telling you, man,
I don't know.

18:28.890 --> 18:30.631
- All right, listen.

18:30.674 --> 18:32.937
If you think of something
that might be useful,

18:32.981 --> 18:35.810
give me a call.

18:39.379 --> 18:40.815
We got a hit
on that black car?

18:40.858 --> 18:42.730
- Yeah, pulled video
from a traffic cam

18:42.773 --> 18:43.818
two blocks south of the church.

18:43.861 --> 18:45.124
- You run the plates?

18:45.167 --> 18:47.865
- Yep, it came back
to a 2004 Grand Cherokee.

18:47.909 --> 18:50.868
It's registered to a female
Hispanic, 29 years of age.

18:50.912 --> 18:53.219
She goes by the name
Anna Salgado.

18:53.262 --> 18:55.351
She lives at 6438 South Homan,

18:55.395 --> 18:57.179
and she does have
a sheet, boss.

18:57.223 --> 18:59.138
Got pinched
for a drug misdemeanor.

18:59.181 --> 19:01.923
- She also has a brother doing
three years for a felony

19:01.966 --> 19:03.620
and a daughter,
seven years old.

19:03.664 --> 19:05.144
Guess who the father is.

19:05.187 --> 19:06.710
Carlos Infante.

19:06.754 --> 19:08.712
- The banger hiding his cash
at the church.

19:08.756 --> 19:11.237
- Nice work.
All right, bring her in.

19:12.412 --> 19:13.804
- I already told you.

19:13.848 --> 19:15.284
I don't know anything about
no robbery at no church.

19:15.328 --> 19:17.243
- We got a warrant
for your phone.

19:17.286 --> 19:19.636
We read all your texts.

19:19.680 --> 19:21.334
Look, I know what's going on.

19:21.377 --> 19:22.770
- What's that mean?

19:22.813 --> 19:24.728
- It means that I know you
and your baby daddy,

19:24.772 --> 19:26.730
Carlos Infante,
have been beefing about money

19:26.774 --> 19:28.384
'cause he hasn't been providing
for your daughter.

19:28.428 --> 19:29.516
- But you're a good mom,

19:29.559 --> 19:30.952
so you took matters
into your own hands,

19:30.995 --> 19:32.214
took what you thought
was yours.

19:32.258 --> 19:33.911
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

19:33.955 --> 19:35.130
- Come on, Anna.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.740
You and Carlos were together
a long time.

19:36.784 --> 19:39.874
You knew he was hiding money
at the church.

19:39.917 --> 19:41.136
Maybe he told you,

19:41.180 --> 19:42.746
maybe you overheard him
talking one day,

19:42.790 --> 19:44.357
but either way, you knew.

19:44.400 --> 19:47.142
- Now we know you're not
a criminal, we know that.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.318
You don't know how
to rob people.

19:49.362 --> 19:51.712
You told one of your friends
about this, right?

19:51.755 --> 19:53.235
A friend came through,

19:53.279 --> 19:56.630
did the robbery,
took the cash,

19:56.673 --> 19:58.240
jumped in your black Jeep,

19:58.284 --> 20:00.111
drove away.

20:00.155 --> 20:02.810
- Like I said, I don't know
what you're talking about.

20:02.853 --> 20:05.378
- You understand
a little girl was shot

20:05.421 --> 20:08.772
about the same age
as your daughter?

20:08.816 --> 20:12.123
She's fighting for her life.

20:13.212 --> 20:14.778
Now you tell us
who was driving your car,

20:14.822 --> 20:15.953
we can work out a deal,

20:15.997 --> 20:18.129
keep you out of prison--

20:18.173 --> 20:20.393
keep you at home
with your little girl

20:20.436 --> 20:23.657
instead of her growing up
in foster care.

20:25.441 --> 20:28.314
Now who was driving your car?

20:28.357 --> 20:31.317
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:31.360 --> 20:35.408
<i>♪ </i>

20:35.451 --> 20:37.888
- Somebody must've stolen it,
or maybe--

20:37.932 --> 20:39.063
- Don't be stupid!

20:39.107 --> 20:40.804
- I'm done talking!
I want a lawyer.

20:52.425 --> 20:54.644
- How'd it go?
- Didn't say a word.

20:54.688 --> 20:57.125
- Yeah, and for good measure,
she lawyered up.

20:57.168 --> 20:59.910
- You got enough to charge her?
- Not even close.

20:59.954 --> 21:01.782
Look, we do know
that she's involved.

21:01.825 --> 21:03.784
She tipped somebody off.

21:03.827 --> 21:05.873
So let's get eyes on her.
Set up outside her house.

21:05.916 --> 21:07.788
Find out who
she's hanging out with.

21:09.964 --> 21:11.313
- I'm not gonna lie to you,
man,

21:11.357 --> 21:13.359
I'm, like, a little impressed
with this Anna girl.

21:13.402 --> 21:16.318
I would've bet $1,000
she was gonna roll.

21:16.362 --> 21:17.711
So that says what?

21:17.754 --> 21:20.409
The shooter's gotta be
her boyfriend or a relative?

21:20.453 --> 21:21.976
Someone she cares about, right?

21:22.019 --> 21:24.065
Someone she can't just
snitch on.

21:24.108 --> 21:25.849
'Cause I'm telling you,
Voight,

21:25.893 --> 21:27.808
he made her a hell of an offer.

21:27.851 --> 21:29.070
No jailtime,
gets to keep her daughter,

21:29.113 --> 21:31.420
and this girl, man, she just...
[whistles]

21:31.464 --> 21:33.466
Stayed stoneface.
She didn't even flinch.

21:33.509 --> 21:35.816
- I get it, bro.

21:35.859 --> 21:37.339
She's a hero.

21:37.383 --> 21:39.776
Didn't roll on her homies.

21:39.820 --> 21:41.038
- What you talking about?

21:41.082 --> 21:41.996
- I'm just saying,
if you wanna talk about it,

21:42.039 --> 21:43.084
we can talk about it.

21:43.127 --> 21:44.259
There's no point
in dancing around it.

21:44.303 --> 21:45.216
- I don't actually know
what the hell

21:45.260 --> 21:46.348
you're getting at right now.

21:46.392 --> 21:49.351
- Naw, come on, man, let's...
- Kev.

21:49.395 --> 21:51.179
Are you being serious
right now?

21:51.222 --> 21:54.008
Look at who you're talking to.
It's me.

21:54.051 --> 21:55.357
I'm not talking about you.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.359
I'm talking about
this Anna girl.

21:57.403 --> 22:00.754
She's a single mother;
she's staring down a felony

22:00.797 --> 22:03.104
and is keeping her mouth shut--
that ain't easy.

22:03.147 --> 22:05.193
That's all I'm getting at here.

22:05.236 --> 22:08.196
You did what you did,
and I have no issues with it.

22:08.239 --> 22:09.328
- You sure about that?

22:09.371 --> 22:12.418
- Absolutely.
Hear me when I say that.

22:16.552 --> 22:18.859
- Sorry, I--I just...

22:18.902 --> 22:20.513
- It's all right.
It's all right.

22:20.556 --> 22:22.166
- My bad.

22:22.210 --> 22:23.864
- You got a lot going on.

22:23.907 --> 22:24.995
- [sighs]

22:25.039 --> 22:27.041
- Well, go home.
Get some rest.

22:27.084 --> 22:28.956
All right, I'll stay here
for another hour or so.

22:28.999 --> 22:30.392
I can set up the camera myself.

22:30.436 --> 22:32.002
- All right, all right,
all right, all right.

22:32.046 --> 22:34.178
You gonna be good?
- Yeah.

22:34.222 --> 22:35.832
- [sighs]

22:35.876 --> 22:37.486
- Kev, what'd you end up
doing with the dope?

22:37.530 --> 22:39.445
- I dumped it.

22:39.488 --> 22:40.924
I had to get rid of that.

22:40.968 --> 22:42.143
- Are you sure that was
the right move?

22:42.186 --> 22:44.363
- It was the only move.

22:44.406 --> 22:46.060
Just because people
are marching in the streets

22:46.103 --> 22:48.410
doesn't mean that the world
has changed.

22:48.454 --> 22:50.020
Cops are still blue,

22:50.064 --> 22:52.196
I'm still Black.

22:58.855 --> 23:00.422
<i>- In trying to explain
the situation,</i>

23:00.466 --> 23:04.426
<i>she echoed the same thing I've
heard over and over again:</i>

23:04.470 --> 23:07.168
<i>the George Floyd murder
was the tipping point.</i>

23:07.211 --> 23:09.300
<i>I agree.
[siren blaring]</i>

23:09.344 --> 23:11.302
<i>We all saw that white cop
with his knee on his neck.</i>

23:11.346 --> 23:13.435
<i>- Plus all the other stuff
going on.</i>

23:13.479 --> 23:15.089
<i>Again, the virus,
the shutdown...</i>

23:21.530 --> 23:24.533
<i>[radio droning indistinctly]</i>

23:29.103 --> 23:32.106
[crickets chirping]

23:39.026 --> 23:40.897
- Hey, I'm police.
What's up, guy?

23:40.941 --> 23:43.073
- You ran the stop sign.
- What are you talking about?

23:43.117 --> 23:44.292
- Sir, you ran the stop sign.

23:44.335 --> 23:46.903
That's the reason
we pulled you over.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.471
- No, I didn't
run a stop sign.

23:49.515 --> 23:51.865
I guess y'all just bored?

23:51.908 --> 23:53.475
Saw a brother driving
a decent car,

23:53.519 --> 23:55.042
figured you pull his ass over,
have some fun?

23:55.085 --> 23:56.260
- Hey, take it easy.

23:56.304 --> 23:57.566
My partner said
he saw you run a stop sign.

23:57.610 --> 24:00.003
We had no idea
if you were Black or white.

24:00.047 --> 24:01.309
- Step out of the car.

24:01.352 --> 24:03.137
- Look, I'm police.

24:03.180 --> 24:06.183
My name's Kevin Atwater,
badge number 52784.

24:06.227 --> 24:07.576
I work with
the intelligence unit.

24:07.620 --> 24:09.099
Y'all can check
whatever you want.

24:09.143 --> 24:10.492
- I said,
step out of the vehicle.

24:10.536 --> 24:11.798
- [sighs]

24:11.841 --> 24:14.453
Nah, I'm not stepping out
of no damn vehicle,

24:14.496 --> 24:17.281
but I will show you my badge
nice and slow.

24:17.325 --> 24:19.022
Okay, so y'all can--

24:19.066 --> 24:22.025
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:22.069 --> 24:27.161
<i>♪ </i>

24:27.204 --> 24:30.207
Okay, look, fellas,
I'm stepping out of the car.

24:32.035 --> 24:33.210
- Shut the door.

24:33.254 --> 24:35.865
- I'm shutting the door.
My hands are high.

24:38.041 --> 24:39.652
You see my star and my gun.

24:39.695 --> 24:42.219
If you look in my left pocket,
you'll find my ID.

24:48.574 --> 24:50.271
- He's telling the truth.

24:50.314 --> 24:52.969
He's the police, Ron.

24:54.362 --> 24:56.016
- So what you a cop?

24:56.059 --> 24:57.234
I got an anonymous tip

24:57.278 --> 24:58.540
that a guy was selling drugs
in this car.

24:58.584 --> 25:00.281
- What are you talking about?

25:00.324 --> 25:02.892
- The guy sold a kilo of heroin
to a dirty cop in a blue Dodge.

25:04.328 --> 25:05.460
- You with Nolan's crew?

25:09.551 --> 25:12.554
Well, search the car, Ron.
Look wherever you want,

25:12.598 --> 25:13.947
but you ain't gonna find
a damn thing

25:13.990 --> 25:15.992
'cause I already
found the dope.

25:16.036 --> 25:18.299
It was in the trunk.

25:20.083 --> 25:22.042
Is this really
what you wanna do,

25:22.085 --> 25:24.131
Black man?

25:24.174 --> 25:27.134
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:27.177 --> 25:34.184
<i>♪ </i>

25:40.103 --> 25:41.757
- [sighs]

25:41.801 --> 25:42.976
You wanted to see me?

25:43.019 --> 25:44.891
- Yeah.

25:44.934 --> 25:46.588
Shut the door.

25:50.679 --> 25:52.812
So I heard you got
into a beef last night

25:52.855 --> 25:54.553
with a couple patrol officers.

25:54.596 --> 25:55.902
- More complicated than that.

25:55.945 --> 25:58.078
- I'm sure it is.

25:58.121 --> 26:00.776
- One of Nolan's boys
pulled me over last night

26:00.820 --> 26:03.823
hoping to find dope in my car.

26:03.866 --> 26:05.172
- Dope?

26:05.215 --> 26:07.435
- They planted a kilo
of heroin in my car.

26:07.478 --> 26:09.437
- Why didn't you tell me?

26:09.480 --> 26:11.395
- Didn't want
to get you involved.

26:11.439 --> 26:12.571
- Mm.
[chuckles]

26:12.614 --> 26:15.008
Okay.

26:15.051 --> 26:17.880
So tell me, what's your plan?
Hmm?

26:17.924 --> 26:20.666
Going to IED?

26:20.709 --> 26:23.059
- I can't prove
they planted the dope

26:23.103 --> 26:25.801
or that they're even
harassing me.

26:25.845 --> 26:27.934
So I'll just sit back
and wait for one of these punks

26:27.977 --> 26:31.154
to screw up and leave behind
some actual evidence.

26:31.198 --> 26:33.026
Don't really have
any other options.

26:33.069 --> 26:35.550
- Sure you do.

26:38.205 --> 26:40.686
Kevin...

26:40.729 --> 26:42.426
[sighs]

26:42.470 --> 26:45.691
The blue wall
is a tricky thing.

26:45.734 --> 26:49.564
It's not a person or an object.
It's a code.

26:49.608 --> 26:51.435
You never really see it.

26:51.479 --> 26:53.699
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:53.742 --> 26:56.223
I mean, it's there,
but it's not there.

26:56.266 --> 26:58.704
You understand?

26:59.879 --> 27:03.447
It's like trying
to fight a ghost, Kevin.

27:03.491 --> 27:06.929
<i>♪ </i>

27:06.973 --> 27:08.844
- I know, Sarge.

27:08.888 --> 27:11.455
- Hmm.

27:12.108 --> 27:15.242
- I just wanna do this my way.

27:15.285 --> 27:22.466
<i>♪ </i>

27:23.554 --> 27:26.079
- Okay, so where we at
with Anna Salgado?

27:26.122 --> 27:28.821
- Not sure--I'm meeting up
with Ruzek right now

27:28.864 --> 27:30.910
to check out
surveillance video.

27:30.953 --> 27:33.173
- Hit it.

27:41.311 --> 27:42.922
- You know these guys
are pushing their luck.

27:42.965 --> 27:44.663
They need to know that.
- I told you, I'm good.

27:44.706 --> 27:46.795
- No.
- It's over.

27:46.839 --> 27:47.927
- Are you gonna talk
to this punk Gaffney,

27:47.970 --> 27:49.102
or am I gonna talk to him,
seriously?

27:49.145 --> 27:51.539
- Yo, check it out.

27:55.891 --> 27:58.764
- All right, well, let's run it
through facial rec.

27:58.807 --> 28:00.113
- Mm-hmm.

28:00.156 --> 28:01.810
- Miguel Cortez,
he's a career punk.

28:01.854 --> 28:03.682
He's got five priors,
two armed robberies,

28:03.725 --> 28:05.509
two ag bats,
one attempted murder,

28:05.553 --> 28:06.815
six or seven drug charges.

28:06.859 --> 28:07.947
- Hailey...
- Yeah.

28:07.990 --> 28:08.948
- Pull up
the surveillance video

28:08.991 --> 28:10.819
from the church.

28:12.734 --> 28:14.040
Okay.

28:14.083 --> 28:15.955
Is that Miguel?

28:15.998 --> 28:18.522
- Looks like him.
Same height, same build.

28:18.566 --> 28:20.089
It's just not clear enough.
- Yeah, but come on.

28:20.133 --> 28:22.526
We all know it's him.
It makes perfect sense.

28:22.570 --> 28:23.919
He's dating Anna,

28:23.963 --> 28:25.747
she's complaining about
not getting child support,

28:25.791 --> 28:27.096
she gets fed up,

28:27.140 --> 28:28.315
she tells Miguel
where the dope money's stashed

28:28.358 --> 28:29.446
at St. Angela's.

28:29.490 --> 28:30.926
- Yeah, and he grabs
a gun and a mask.

28:30.970 --> 28:32.145
He sets out to commit the
easiest robbery of his life.

28:32.188 --> 28:33.320
- Exactly.

28:33.363 --> 28:35.931
- Hey, good news.
After we ID'd Miguel,

28:35.975 --> 28:37.759
we pulled video
of his last known address.

28:37.803 --> 28:39.282
- Good.

28:39.326 --> 28:41.632
- That's Miguel entering
his house

28:41.676 --> 28:43.765
45 minutes after
the robbery and shooting.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.332
- Same pants and shoes,

28:45.375 --> 28:46.942
and he's carrying the same bag
we saw in the other video.

28:46.986 --> 28:48.814
- So let's get a warrant.
Scoop his ass up.

28:48.857 --> 28:49.858
- Right.

28:56.343 --> 28:58.127
- I've got up top.

29:01.652 --> 29:02.784
- Did you hear him?

29:02.828 --> 29:04.177
Announce your office
and hit that door.

29:04.220 --> 29:05.787
Be ready.

29:05.831 --> 29:08.790
<i>[exciting music]</i>

29:08.834 --> 29:15.057
<i>♪ </i>

29:15.101 --> 29:17.712
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Upstairs window.

29:17.756 --> 29:20.062
We just got made.

29:20.933 --> 29:22.717
Chicago PD!

29:22.761 --> 29:24.110
Hey, put your hands
on the table.

29:24.153 --> 29:25.372
Hands on the table.

29:25.415 --> 29:26.721
Ma'am, walk towards me.
Walk towards me.

29:26.765 --> 29:28.027
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

29:28.070 --> 29:29.376
Sit down.
Put your hands on the table.

29:29.419 --> 29:30.943
both: Hands on the table.
- Come on.

29:30.986 --> 29:32.814
- I got you.
Go.

29:32.858 --> 29:35.077
[indistinct shouting]

29:35.121 --> 29:36.818
- All right, it's all right.

29:36.862 --> 29:38.341
- Stop, put your hands on
your head and walk towards me.

29:38.385 --> 29:40.126
- Ruz, I got a runner!
- Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

29:41.780 --> 29:44.043
- Hey!

29:44.086 --> 29:45.261
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

29:45.305 --> 29:46.741
- It's over, Miguel.

29:46.785 --> 29:48.351
Get your hands up.

29:48.395 --> 29:49.875
Now.

29:49.918 --> 29:52.965
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:53.008 --> 29:55.402
<i>♪ </i>

29:55.445 --> 29:56.664
- Be smart, man.

29:56.707 --> 29:57.839
Put your hands up
nice and high.

29:57.883 --> 29:59.014
Don't make this hard
on yourself.

29:59.058 --> 30:00.711
- You wanna die?

30:00.755 --> 30:03.758
<i>♪ </i>

30:03.802 --> 30:06.108
'Cause I won't ask again.

30:11.897 --> 30:14.116
- Hands behind your back.

30:16.292 --> 30:17.903
- Here we go.

30:17.946 --> 30:20.209
We got about 50K in here,
maybe more.

30:20.253 --> 30:21.950
Best part is,

30:21.994 --> 30:24.344
Miguel left it
in the church collection bag.

30:24.387 --> 30:26.215
The St. Angela's logo
on it and everything.

30:26.259 --> 30:27.303
- Nice.

30:27.347 --> 30:28.739
Book it into evidence,
will you?

30:28.783 --> 30:30.393
- Copy that.

30:30.437 --> 30:33.440
- You talked to Kev about
all this Doyle business?

30:33.483 --> 30:35.268
- A little.
You?

30:35.311 --> 30:37.661
- I'm trying.
He's shutting me out.

30:37.705 --> 30:39.663
- He's having a hard time,
boss.

30:39.707 --> 30:41.709
These guys,
they're playing too rough.

30:41.752 --> 30:44.059
- They're just
getting started.

30:44.103 --> 30:45.931
- He did what he had to do.

30:45.974 --> 30:48.063
It's different for him.
It just is.

30:48.107 --> 30:50.936
You know, being a Black cop
here in Chicago these days.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.155
- Hmm.
- Can't be easy.

30:59.118 --> 31:00.336
- Go on in.

31:04.993 --> 31:07.082
- Ma'am.

31:07.126 --> 31:08.823
- We got a problem.

31:08.867 --> 31:10.781
- Kay, I don't know
what you're talking about.

31:13.436 --> 31:15.047
- I just watched
the bodycam footage

31:15.090 --> 31:16.657
of Miguel Cortez's arrest.

31:16.700 --> 31:19.312
You kicked down the damn door
without announcing your office.

31:19.355 --> 31:20.879
- That's because we got made.

31:20.922 --> 31:22.793
- I just spoke to the
state's attorney's office.

31:22.837 --> 31:24.926
They've determined
the entry improper,

31:24.970 --> 31:27.842
so all the evidence recovered
is inadmissible.

31:27.886 --> 31:29.148
- Okay, look, I get it.

31:29.191 --> 31:32.238
Nobody wants to hand out
no-knocks these days.

31:32.281 --> 31:34.327
We had a warrant
to enter the premises

31:34.370 --> 31:35.806
and apprehend the offender.

31:35.850 --> 31:37.939
- You're not hearing me.

31:37.983 --> 31:39.854
You entered the premises

31:39.898 --> 31:42.030
without announcing your office.

31:42.074 --> 31:44.206
There were women and children
in there.

31:44.250 --> 31:46.121
It could've gone bad
a hundred different ways.

31:46.165 --> 31:48.167
- But it didn't.

31:48.210 --> 31:50.082
- Like I said before, Sergeant,

31:50.125 --> 31:52.345
I want you to succeed
more than you know.

31:52.388 --> 31:54.173
- [chuckles]

31:54.216 --> 31:57.176
- But the days
of playing God are over.

31:57.219 --> 31:59.265
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

31:59.308 --> 32:01.920
The quicker you understand
that, the better.

32:01.963 --> 32:05.010
<i>♪ </i>

32:05.053 --> 32:06.794
[door slams]

32:10.798 --> 32:12.756
- Right or wrong,
there's nothing we can do.

32:12.800 --> 32:14.323
All the evidence
has been tossed.

32:14.367 --> 32:15.890
- You guys, I'm sorry.
I saw the blinds move.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.283
I don't know what
I was supposed to do.

32:17.326 --> 32:18.849
- Adam, no, listen to me,
you did the right thing.

32:18.893 --> 32:20.895
What I'm trying to tell you is,
it doesn't matter.

32:20.939 --> 32:22.331
You get it?

32:22.375 --> 32:24.159
The reality is,

32:24.203 --> 32:26.640
no one's got the guts to
stand up for police right now.

32:26.683 --> 32:29.599
Not the mayor, not the white
shirts in the ivory tower.

32:29.643 --> 32:31.427
No one.

32:31.471 --> 32:33.342
Get used to it.

32:35.518 --> 32:37.607
Okay, so...

32:37.651 --> 32:39.914
the only real evidence
we have now

32:39.958 --> 32:41.481
is that video of Miguel
entering his house

32:41.524 --> 32:43.178
carrying the bag.

32:43.222 --> 32:44.658
- Same bag he was carrying when
he tried to shoot the priest.

32:44.701 --> 32:47.182
- Yeah, I get it, but try
proving it's the same bag.

32:47.226 --> 32:49.793
I mean, a black bag
is a black bag.

32:49.837 --> 32:52.535
We gotta start all over
from the beginning,

32:52.579 --> 32:54.842
build a whole new case.

32:54.885 --> 32:56.887
So find more
surveillance video,

32:56.931 --> 32:59.020
new witnesses.

32:59.064 --> 33:00.848
Meantime, I'm gonna
talk to Miguel.

33:00.891 --> 33:03.285
I can still let him know
how much evidence we have.

33:05.331 --> 33:07.289
For God's sakes, bro,

33:07.333 --> 33:10.553
the collection bags
are marked St. Angela's.

33:10.597 --> 33:13.643
It doesn't get any better
than that.

33:18.474 --> 33:20.781
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

33:24.828 --> 33:27.875
- Your girlfriend told you
about the money

33:27.918 --> 33:31.487
because Carlos stopped
providing for their daughter,

33:31.531 --> 33:32.706
and honestly?

33:32.749 --> 33:34.447
I don't even blame her.

33:35.578 --> 33:37.450
I mean, that guy makes
a lot of money selling dope.

33:37.493 --> 33:39.452
Least he can do
is break off a few grand

33:39.495 --> 33:41.758
every month
for his little girl.

33:41.802 --> 33:43.978
- I told you.
I didn't do it.

33:44.022 --> 33:46.241
- You stole the money,
you ran out,

33:46.285 --> 33:48.026
the priest chased after you,

33:48.069 --> 33:50.332
he tried to tackle you,

33:50.376 --> 33:52.639
so you opened fire.

33:52.682 --> 33:54.771
That's what happened.

33:54.815 --> 33:57.078
You know, the fact
that you were so close

33:57.122 --> 33:59.037
and you missed,

33:59.080 --> 34:02.605
that tells me you probably
just trying to scare the guy.

34:04.651 --> 34:07.306
But see,
the problem is, Miguel,

34:07.349 --> 34:10.961
the reason we're all so upset

34:11.005 --> 34:13.834
is one of your bullets
hit a 5-year-old girl.

34:15.618 --> 34:19.100
She's fighting for her life
right now at Chicago Med.

34:19.144 --> 34:22.277
- Chicago is a--
it's a dangerous place.

34:27.761 --> 34:30.720
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

34:30.764 --> 34:35.073
<i>♪ </i>

34:35.116 --> 34:38.424
- You confess to the robbery

34:38.467 --> 34:41.905
and the shooting,

34:41.949 --> 34:43.472
you can cut yourself a deal.

34:43.516 --> 34:44.647
You understand?

34:44.691 --> 34:47.389
But you wait,
play the long game,

34:47.433 --> 34:50.523
you try and take
this thing to trial,

34:50.566 --> 34:54.004
state's attorney is gonna
nail your ass to a cross.

34:54.048 --> 34:55.615
[phone buzzing]

34:55.658 --> 34:58.313
- I want my lawyer.
- What is the matter with you?

34:58.357 --> 35:01.360
- Yo, I'm done talking!

35:01.403 --> 35:08.410
<i>♪ </i>

35:11.979 --> 35:13.067
- Hey.

35:13.111 --> 35:14.938
Heard what happened
with the search.

35:14.982 --> 35:16.984
- Yeah, well, it is what it is.
- New world.

35:17.027 --> 35:19.421
Everybody's paying attention to
the fine print all of a sudden.

35:19.465 --> 35:21.684
- Where is he?
- In there.

35:24.774 --> 35:28.343
- Mr. Diaz, what can I
do for you?

35:28.387 --> 35:30.128
- You tell me
you caught the person

35:30.171 --> 35:31.694
who killed my little girl.

35:33.870 --> 35:35.002
- You're saying...

35:35.045 --> 35:36.873
- She died an hour ago.

35:36.917 --> 35:39.006
- [whispering]
Oh, my God.

35:39.049 --> 35:42.357
I'm--I'm so sorry.

35:42.401 --> 35:44.794
- Did you arrest the killer?

35:44.838 --> 35:47.493
- We're still working on that,

35:47.536 --> 35:49.495
but the good news is,

35:49.538 --> 35:51.061
we know who did it.

35:51.105 --> 35:53.412
We just need a little more
evidence, build a better case.

35:53.455 --> 35:55.588
- If you know who did it,
isn't that enough?

35:55.631 --> 35:58.373
Doesn't that mean you already
have a good case?

35:59.548 --> 36:01.115
- Sometimes the law
is complicated.

36:01.159 --> 36:03.422
- No, it's simple.

36:03.465 --> 36:05.685
It is real simple.

36:05.728 --> 36:07.643
So who killed her?
Who killed her?

36:07.687 --> 36:08.862
Who is he?
- I can't tell you that.

36:08.905 --> 36:10.037
- Who is he?
Where is he?

36:10.080 --> 36:11.212
If you don't take care of this,
I will!

36:11.256 --> 36:12.518
- Sir, please!

36:12.561 --> 36:15.129
- No.
My little girl is dead.

36:15.173 --> 36:17.087
And I want that son of a bitch
who killed her to go down,

36:17.131 --> 36:19.089
to pay for what he did!
- So do I.

36:19.133 --> 36:23.093
And I promise you I will do
everything I can.

36:23.137 --> 36:25.705
But it's, it's just...

36:25.748 --> 36:28.708
<i>[somber music]</i>

36:28.751 --> 36:35.758
<i>♪ </i>

36:44.724 --> 36:47.553
Grab Miguel
and put him in a cage.

36:47.596 --> 36:49.816
- Boss, you sure
that's a good idea?

36:53.515 --> 36:55.865
- Excuse me?
- Sarge, I mean...

36:55.909 --> 36:57.040
come on,
things are different now.

36:57.084 --> 36:58.085
I'll do what
you need me to do--

36:58.128 --> 37:00.479
- Laura Diaz just died.

37:00.522 --> 37:01.958
Five years old.

37:03.699 --> 37:05.092
The prick who
pulled the trigger's

37:05.135 --> 37:06.180
sitting right in there.

37:06.224 --> 37:08.138
- Doesn't matter.

37:09.836 --> 37:12.969
- Of course it matters.
He killed her.

37:13.013 --> 37:14.667
- I know he did,
we all know he did,

37:14.710 --> 37:16.582
but we can't just drag his ass
down to a cage.

37:16.625 --> 37:17.931
We done with all that--

37:17.974 --> 37:20.020
- Oh, yeah, says who?
- Guys, let's not do this.

37:20.063 --> 37:21.195
- Says me.

37:21.239 --> 37:22.631
- You calling the shots now,
Kev?

37:22.675 --> 37:24.938
- No, but I know we can't keep
bringing people down

37:24.981 --> 37:26.113
to a cage and beating they ass

37:26.156 --> 37:27.810
because we think
they know something

37:27.854 --> 37:30.248
or did something.
Those days are over.

37:30.291 --> 37:31.858
- You don't like the way
I do business?

37:31.901 --> 37:33.947
I'm not woke enough for you?

37:33.990 --> 37:35.905
You feel free
to get the hell out.

37:35.949 --> 37:37.907
- Well, Sarge,
this is your unit.

37:37.951 --> 37:39.648
I'm proud to work here,

37:39.692 --> 37:41.041
but things
have definitely changed.

37:41.084 --> 37:42.564
That means that
we gotta change too.

37:42.608 --> 37:44.566
- Yeah, you wanna be
a Boy Scout?

37:44.610 --> 37:45.828
You wanna be a Boy Scout!?

37:45.872 --> 37:49.005
Maybe you should get
yourself another job!

37:49.049 --> 37:51.181
I'll tell you what,
you're right about one thing--

37:51.225 --> 37:53.227
this is my unit!

37:53.271 --> 37:56.012
And in my unit,
we do what we gotta do

37:56.056 --> 37:59.015
to put bad guys away!

37:59.059 --> 38:01.844
Whatever it takes!

38:01.888 --> 38:04.847
<i>[solemn music]</i>

38:04.891 --> 38:11.680
<i>♪ </i>

39:23.752 --> 39:26.712
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:26.755 --> 39:33.762
<i>♪ </i>

39:55.393 --> 39:58.787
[man whistles]

39:58.831 --> 40:01.790
<i>[ominous music]</i>

40:01.834 --> 40:08.841
<i>♪ </i>

40:10.669 --> 40:13.149
- Hey!
[all grunting]

40:13.193 --> 40:16.457
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:16.501 --> 40:23.638
<i>♪ </i>

40:27.816 --> 40:31.298
[car engine turns over]

40:31.341 --> 40:34.344
[tires squeal]

40:39.349 --> 40:42.352
- [grunts]
[heavy breathing]

40:43.876 --> 40:45.878
[groans]

40:47.096 --> 40:50.099
[panting]

41:10.511 --> 41:13.427
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:13.471 --> 41:20.478
<i>♪ </i>

41:39.888 --> 41:42.891
[wolf howls]
